Manchester United target Miranda has revealed his delight at being linked with a move to Louis van Gaal 's side but insists he is keen on staying at Atletico Madrid . The Brazilian centre back is said to be on Van Gaal 's summer wishlist as the Dutchman is keen on strengthening his defensive options ahead of the 2015-16 campaign . However the Manchester United boss may find it difficult in prising the 30-year-old away from Atletico Madrid as he insists he is content with life at the Vicente Calderon . Manchester United are said to be keeping a close eye on Atletico Madrid defender Miranda . Miranda -LRB- centre -RRB- has admitted he is ` proud ' to be linked with a move to Manchester United . Miranda , speaking to Estadao , said of speculation linking him with a move to Old Trafford : ` Of course this news reaches me , and it makes me happy . It shows I am doing well . ` It makes me proud , but my intention is to stay at Atletico because I still have a year and a half on my contract . ' Miranda has started Brazil 's last eight matches since narrowly missing out on a chance of representing his country at the 2014 World Cup . However the 30-year-old has revealed he is keen on seeing out his contract at Atletico Madrid .